title: FASCISTS michael mann 2004 (non fiction book)
description:
MICHAEL MANN:   "FASCISTS"   (2004)



One of the best anglosaxon sociologists studies the curious continental tribe 

called fascists , who came to power in roumania , spain , italy , germany in the 

1930s and needed less than a decade to destroy Europe and  half of the world , which 

is one of the reasons because of this ideology is today not much beloved.















NOTA BENE: Here in Spain we use the word "facha" for a member of this curious tribe
